{
  "text": "It is a SRRL-type 1.5-cell thermionic cathode rf gun with nose cone on the cathode assembly. This nose cone is intended to focus the space charge beam in the half-cell in its original design. And this nose cone will be removed from the cathode assembly (i.e. a flat surface cathode) in our 2998 MHz gun for better electron distribution after bunch compression. Field ratio of this rf gun has been adjusted to two for generation of linear beam distribution in the longitudinal phase space for bunch compression with the alpha magnet down stream [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The cathode has been activated to 1100 \u00b0C in its surface temperature and has been operated at ~950 \u00b0C during beam test. The correspondence between cathode temperature and heater power are measured with a pyrometer.",
  "citation_candidates": [
